Drag and drop the Python code from the left onto the correct step on the right to call a REST API.
Select and Place:
//IMG//

A developer is working on a branch called topic that was created from the master branch to add a new feature to the product. After making a few commits on the branch, the developer wants to compare the changes between the topic and the master branches. Which two Git commands are used? (Choose two.)

discussion.content:
Selected Answer: BE
B and E are correct.
B. git diff topic...master - This command compares the changes between the common ancestor of the two branches (usually where they diverged) and the tip of each branch.

E. git diff topic master - This command compares the changes between the tips of the two branches directly.

comments.content: HEAD refers to the current branch’s latest commit, so this would compare topic with itself or an unrelated commit.

discussion.content:
Selected Answer: CE
git diff [<options>] [--merge-base] <commit> [--] [<path>…]
This form is to view the changes you have in your working tree relative to the named <commit>. You can use HEAD to compare it with the latest commit, or a branch name to compare with the tip of a different branch.

questions.question_text: What is a capability of Cisco UCS Director?

discussion.content:
Selected Answer: B
B is correct

A is wrong - it doesn't support ALL network hardware equipment
C is wrong - UCS Director can be used for multi-vendor environments
D is wrong - it handles network, security, virtualization, OS, storage, etc.

choices.C: It supports only hardware created by Cisco to ensure scalability across the network.
choices.A: It is used to generate workflow reports on any hardware equipment in the network.
choices.D: It is a platform for monitoring and troubleshooting server-related issues.
choices.B: It is used to create multistep workflows to automate large and repetitive tasks.
